Subsequently, the fluorescent titration of TPFP to HClO is investigated in the mixture of PBS buffer (pH=5.5, 10mM) and EtOH (v/v, 5/1) at 25°C, as is shown in Fig. 1
                        A. As is seen from the figure, the fluorescence enhancement is directly proportional to the increase of HClO concentration. In addition, a linear relationship between the fluorescence intensity (I538
                        ) and the concentration of HClO is observed in the range of 0–5.0μM (Fig. 1B). In this case, the detection limit (S/N=3) is determined to be 5.7nM (Fig. S7), which is lower than the commonly used method API-MS, i.e., 57.1nM (3 ppb). Moreover, the change of fluorescence lifetimes of TPFP before and after the addition of HClO is also measured. As is illustrated in Fig. S8, the lifetime of TPFP at 538nm is enhanced from 2.03 to 2.95ns after the addition of 5μM of HClO, implying the inhibition of PET process in the presence of HClO.
